<title type="html"><![CDATA[W3's 'role' attribute provides accessibility features]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=22&amp;p=140#p140"><![CDATA[
I found a good reason for the introduction of predefined roles in W3's specification. It provides accessibility features. See: <a href="http://www.alistapart.com/articles/waiaria" class="postlink">Accessible Web 2.0 Applications with WAI-ARIA</a><br /><br />Its assistive technology like &quot;Aural stylesheets&quot; but this one is for HTML. Someone should take note of this.  <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_idea.gif" alt=":idea:" title="Idea" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Fri Apr 20, 2007 4:35 pm</p><hr />
