<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=22&amp;p=117#p117"><![CDATA[
But it doesn't have to be a new tag -- just a new attribute, '<span style="color: green">role</span>' or similar. (The W3C's new initiative is using <span style="color: green">role</span>, that's why i'm using it for my example.<br /><br />So for instance, my paragraph might look like this:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;p class=&quot;someclass&quot; role=&quot;address&quot;&gt;Text&lt;/p&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />See? No overloading.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">adrienne</a> — Thu Apr 12, 2007 2:29 pm</p><hr />
