<title type="html"><![CDATA[overload of class attribute?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=22&amp;p=115#p115"><![CDATA[
I know this topic has been raised in several places around the web, but i can't find anyone on the mailing list archive speaking to it (this may be a reflection of my searching rather than of anything else). <br /><br />Is it really a good idea to overload <span style="color: green">class</span> with structured content? What do you all think of the W3C's very similar proposal to structure content, using the new proposed <span style="color: green">role</span> attribute? <br /><br />I think that having a new enumerated attribute seems like a WAY better idea than overloading an attribute that people are already using for a number of other things.<br /><br />Just hoping to get a discussion started somewhere about this!<br /><br />Thanks,<br />Adrienne Leigh Travis<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">adrienne</a> — Wed Apr 11, 2007 4:50 pm</p><hr />
